<TITLE> Human-chain demo demands mutiny killers' punishment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 6 (bdnews24.com)  Families of the army officers killed unarmed in the border guards' mutiny staged a human-chain demonstration Friday to demand a fair inquiry to hunt down and try the perpetrators of the grisly bloodbath. Teary-eyed children and other family members lined along the street from Jahangir Gate to the BAF Shahin College gate for two hours from 10am to urge people from across the broad social spectrum to get behind the national demand. School students from Dhaka Cantonment and retired army officers also joined the human chain in an emotional show of solidarity for the common cause. also A mourning procession was brought out by the in the city demanding immediate arrest and trial of the perpetrators and the mastermind of the mutiny. They waved placards that said, 'Severe punishment for killers demanded'. Later, after Juma prayers, the families laid wreaths at the graves of the slain officers at Banani Graveyard and said prayers. In addition, city mosques offered special prayers for the peace of the souls. bd
